WEBVTT

00:00.567 --> 00:04.103
<i>PREVIOUSLY,</i>
<i>ON</i> SIGNED, SEALED, DELIVERED--

00:04.105 --> 00:06.271
HOW WAS YOUR BALLROOM DANCING
SHOWCASE ON FRIDAY?

00:06.273 --> 00:08.007
WE WERE
FORCED TO CANCEL.

00:08.009 --> 00:09.007
THIS IS AN APPLICATION

00:09.009 --> 00:10.075
FOR THE "MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY" PAGEANT!

00:10.077 --> 00:11.276
OLIVER, SHE'S NOT COMING BACK.

00:11.278 --> 00:12.344
HOW DARE YOU?

00:12.346 --> 00:14.213
THIS BIRD HAS FLOWN,
MY FRIEND.

00:14.215 --> 00:15.581
YOU MAY PRESUME TOO MUCH.

00:20.153 --> 00:21.353
THIS WAY.

00:21.355 --> 00:24.023
GOT JUST
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKIN' FOR.

00:25.191 --> 00:26.759
1952 STIGGLEMAN.

00:26.761 --> 00:28.527
[KNOCKING]
SOLID OAK.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.696
LOT OF SCHOOLS USED 'EM
BEFORE THE PLANT CLOSED,

00:30.698 --> 00:32.097
IN AUGHT-SEVEN.

00:35.101 --> 00:37.202
[DRAWER THUMPS AND RATTLES]

00:37.204 --> 00:38.771
IT'S STUCK.

00:45.512 --> 00:47.379
SOMETHING'S
JAMMED IN THE TRACK.

00:48.415 --> 00:49.648
[THUMP]

00:51.751 --> 00:53.619
[TAILGATE BANGS]

00:53.621 --> 00:56.155
[♪]

00:59.059 --> 01:00.225
WHERE'S DILLARD?

01:00.227 --> 01:02.561
RETIRED.
I'M TAKING OVER HIS ROUTE.

01:02.563 --> 01:04.063
ANY OUTGOING?

01:04.065 --> 01:06.198
NAH.

01:06.200 --> 01:07.733
OH, WAIT!

01:07.735 --> 01:10.569
I THINK MAYBE THIS
IS SUPPOSED TO GET SOMEWHERE.

01:12.605 --> 01:14.740
NOT A PROBLEM.

01:14.742 --> 01:16.708
I KNOW EXACTLY
WHO TO GIVE IT TO.

01:18.678 --> 01:21.547
♪ SEND ME LOVE EVERY DAY

01:21.549 --> 01:24.116
♪ AND SEND ME ON MY WAY

01:24.118 --> 01:28.353
♪ DELIVER ME
JUST DELIVER ME ♪

01:29.856 --> 01:32.257
[♪]

01:40.533 --> 01:41.633
SHANE?

01:41.635 --> 01:43.302
-HMM?
IF I'M RETURNING TO SENDER--

01:43.304 --> 01:45.304
...BUT THE SENDER
RETURNED IT TO US,

01:45.306 --> 01:48.107
AND THEN WROTE "RETURN
TO THE RETURNER," THEN--

01:48.109 --> 01:50.242
[SPEAKERS SQUEALING]

01:50.244 --> 01:51.643
WHAT WAS THAT?

01:51.645 --> 01:53.879
THAT IS THE NEW P.A. SYSTEM
THEY INSTALLED LAST NIGHT.

01:53.881 --> 01:55.114
[GLYNIS, ON P.A.]:
<i>GOOD MORNING.</i>

01:55.116 --> 01:57.182
<i>THE TIME IS 8:01 A.M.</i>

01:57.184 --> 01:58.750
<i>IF YOU ARE NOT</i>
<i>AT YOUR WORK STATION,</i>

01:58.752 --> 02:00.719
<i>PLEASE REPORT</i>
<i>TO HUMAN RESOURCES</i>

02:00.721 --> 02:01.854
<i>FOR YOUR EXIT INTERVIEW.</i>

02:01.856 --> 02:03.522
<i>ADDITIONALLY,</i>

02:03.524 --> 02:05.591
<i>THERE WILL BE</i>
<i>A CAKE AND COOKIE RECEPTION</i>

02:05.593 --> 02:08.127
<i>4:00 P.M. TODAY</i>
<i>IN THE EMPLOYEE BREAK ROOM</i>

02:08.129 --> 02:10.129
<i>TO MEET AND GREET THE NEW</i>
<i>DENVER BRANCH SUPERVISOR</i>

02:10.131 --> 02:11.296
<i>GLYNIS RUCKER.</i>

02:11.298 --> 02:12.397
<i>THANK YOU FOR YOUR ATTENTION.</i>

02:12.399 --> 02:13.632
WHO IS THAT?

02:13.634 --> 02:16.602
THE NEW DENVER BRANCH SUPERVISOR
GLYNIS RUCKER.

02:16.604 --> 02:18.203
AH.

02:19.639 --> 02:20.739
WOW.

02:20.741 --> 02:22.574
YOU PEOPLE
ARE HARD TO FIND.

02:22.576 --> 02:24.176
I MEAN,
SO FAR FROM EVERYTHING.

02:24.178 --> 02:26.178
WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT?

02:26.180 --> 02:27.446
YOU MUST BE RITA.

02:27.448 --> 02:30.415
I'VE HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT YOU!
MY NAME IS KIMMI.

02:30.417 --> 02:31.884
KIMMI COOPER!

02:31.886 --> 02:34.319
ANYWAY,
I HAVE A LETTER.

02:34.321 --> 02:35.619
THIS GUY ON MY ROUTE FOUND IT,

02:35.621 --> 02:37.189
BUT THE ADDRESS
IS MOSTLY MISSING, SO.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.757
AH! OKAY. THANK YOU.

02:38.759 --> 02:40.259
IT'S SHANE.
SHANE McINERNEY.

02:40.261 --> 02:41.894
-YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO--
-WHERE'S RITA?

02:43.396 --> 02:45.230
OH. HERE!

02:46.266 --> 02:47.699
[FORCED CHUCKLE]

02:47.701 --> 02:48.800
RITA!

02:48.802 --> 02:50.903
YOU ARE THE TALK
OF THE SORTING FLOOR.

02:50.905 --> 02:53.705
EVERYONE IS SO EXCITED

02:53.707 --> 02:55.340
THAT YOU ARE TRYING OUT
FOR "MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY".

02:55.342 --> 02:56.808
THEY ARE?

02:56.810 --> 02:58.877
[KIMMI]:
YOU ARE <i>SO</i> ADORABLE!

02:58.879 --> 03:00.746
[KIMMI CHUCKLES]
OH!

03:00.748 --> 03:02.848
I HAVE TO KNOW, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING FOR YOUR TALENT?

03:02.850 --> 03:04.716
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA WEAR?
-OOH...

03:04.718 --> 03:06.618
WAS THAT
A LITTLE WEIRD?

03:06.620 --> 03:10.222
DEAD LETTERS ARE PROCESSED
BEFORE WE GET THEM, RIGHT?

03:10.224 --> 03:12.891
MAIL CARRIERS DON'T JUST
WALK THEM THROUGH THE DOOR?

03:12.893 --> 03:15.194
WELL, ACTUALLY, THERE ARE
SEVERAL METHODS WITHIN--

03:15.196 --> 03:16.395
RHETORICAL QUESTION, NORMAN.

03:17.463 --> 03:19.431
AH-HAH! I KNEW IT!

03:19.433 --> 03:20.732
...SOMETHING WITH LACE
AND SOME FRILLS, BUT--

03:20.734 --> 03:21.867
[SHARPLY]: THANK YOU...

03:21.869 --> 03:23.268
KIMMI.

03:23.270 --> 03:24.436
WE CAN TAKE IT FROM HERE.

03:25.505 --> 03:26.772
SEE YOU, RITA.

03:26.774 --> 03:28.840
I JUST KNOW
WE ARE GOING TO BE BEST FRIENDS!

03:28.842 --> 03:30.409
[BOTH GIGGLING]

03:34.581 --> 03:35.647
RITA...

03:35.649 --> 03:36.848
SHE'S NOT YOUR FRIEND.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.617
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.821
THIS... WAS SHOT

03:42.823 --> 03:44.289
AT THE BOISE
"MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY"

03:44.291 --> 03:46.291
AUDITIONS LAST MONTH.

03:47.527 --> 03:49.661
IT'S... <i>KIMMI?</i>

03:49.663 --> 03:52.231
AND HER... TUBA?

03:52.233 --> 03:53.365
[KEY CLACKS]

03:53.367 --> 03:55.500
[KIMMI PLAYS THE TUBA,
FLAT AND STILTED]

03:59.872 --> 04:00.906
SHE WAS HERE

04:00.908 --> 04:02.841
SCOUTING OUT
HER COMPETITION.

04:02.843 --> 04:03.909
WHO?

04:03.911 --> 04:05.444
YOU, RITA!

04:05.446 --> 04:06.678
[GASPS]

04:06.680 --> 04:08.447
MORNING, ALL.

04:09.582 --> 04:12.451
I APOLOGIZE
FOR MY TARDINESS.

04:12.453 --> 04:13.951
I WAS DOING
SOME HOUSECLEANING,

04:13.953 --> 04:16.021
AND I KEPT FINDING THINGS
TO THROW OUT.

04:16.023 --> 04:18.657
[♪]

04:18.659 --> 04:20.659
IT'S FUNNY...

04:20.661 --> 04:22.594
HOW, ONCE YOU START...

04:24.597 --> 04:26.565
IT'S HARD TO STOP.

04:29.369 --> 04:31.837
NOW, FOR THOSE OF YOU
NOT YET INFORMED,

04:31.839 --> 04:34.906
MS. McINERNEY, ON HER OWN
IMPRESSIVE INITIATIVE,

04:34.908 --> 04:37.442
EMPLOYED HER
VAST TECHNOLOGICAL SKILLS

04:37.444 --> 04:39.945
TO DETERMINE
THAT MY WANDERING WIFE

04:39.947 --> 04:41.413
IS QUITE CONTENT

04:41.415 --> 04:43.415
IN HER CURRENT CIRCUMSTANCES
IN PARIS.

04:45.351 --> 04:47.319
I ASSURE YOU, I AM FINE.

04:47.321 --> 04:49.288
WHATEVER LOSS I DO FEEL

04:49.290 --> 04:52.457
IS, OF COURSE, TEMPERED
BY THE WORDS OF SHAKESPEARE--

04:52.459 --> 04:56.528
"LOSS IS NOTHING ELSE BUT CHANGE,

04:56.530 --> 04:59.498
AND CHANGE IS NATURE'S DELIGHT."

04:59.500 --> 05:02.834
I STAND BEFORE YOU...
DELIGHTED.

05:06.873 --> 05:07.906
[TROUBLED SIGH]

05:07.908 --> 05:10.409
POOR OLIVER.
HE IS A MESS!

05:10.411 --> 05:13.045
REALLY?
I-I THOUGHT HE SEEMED PRETTY--

05:13.047 --> 05:14.613
DID YOU
SEE HIS TIE?

05:14.615 --> 05:15.781
WHAT ABOUT IT?

05:15.783 --> 05:18.417
THE KNOT.
IT WAS A FOUR-IN-HAND.

05:18.419 --> 05:20.786
OLIVER USES A FULL WINDSOR
ON WEDNESDAYS.

05:20.788 --> 05:23.689
AND THAT SHAKESPEARE
QUOTE ABOUT CHANGE?

05:23.691 --> 05:25.757
THAT'S NOT SHAKESPEARE!
IT'S MARCUS AURELIUS.

05:25.759 --> 05:27.426
WHO'S GONNA TELL HIM?

05:28.695 --> 05:32.097
THERE. LET'S MOVE ON
TO THE BUSINESS OF THE DAY, HMM?

05:32.099 --> 05:34.066
[♪]

05:50.516 --> 05:51.883
MS. McINERNEY?

05:51.885 --> 05:53.485
WOULD YOU, UH...

05:53.487 --> 05:55.787
PERHAPS DO THE HONOUR
OF SELECTING A LETTER?

05:57.457 --> 05:59.991
ME? OH... UH...

06:02.028 --> 06:04.496
YEAH. Y...

06:04.498 --> 06:06.698
UH... OKAY.

06:11.838 --> 06:15.006
MOST OF THE ADDRESS
HAS BEEN TORN AWAY.

06:15.008 --> 06:17.976
THERE'S NO POSTMARK
OR RETURN ADDRESS.

06:19.612 --> 06:21.380
A "LIBERTY BELL FOREVER" STAMP.

06:21.382 --> 06:23.648
MM. A DESIGN
FIRST ISSUED IN 2007.

06:23.650 --> 06:25.450
IT MEANS THE LETTER
COULD HAVE BEEN WRITTEN

06:25.452 --> 06:26.685
AS LONG AGO
AS SEVEN YEARS,

06:26.687 --> 06:28.019
OR AS RECENTLY
AS YESTERDAY.

06:28.021 --> 06:30.522
THE BLESSING AND THE CURSE
OF THE "FOREVER" STAMP.

06:30.524 --> 06:31.822
[NORMAN]: BLOCK LETTERING.

06:31.824 --> 06:35.927
I'D SAY THIS WAS ADDRESSED
BY A CHILD OF EIGHT TO NINE.

06:35.929 --> 06:37.529
OOH...

06:37.531 --> 06:38.663
PURPLE. A GIRL?

06:38.665 --> 06:40.132
SO...

06:40.134 --> 06:43.135
EVEN IF THIS WAS WRITTEN
SEVEN YEARS AGO,

06:43.137 --> 06:46.438
THE AUTHOR WOULD BE, MM...
15 OR 16 NOW?

06:46.440 --> 06:47.472
PRECISELY.

06:47.474 --> 06:48.673
AND NO DOUBT ON THE CUSP

06:48.675 --> 06:50.976
OF LOSING THEIR NAIVE
AND UNMERITED TRUST

06:50.978 --> 06:53.145
IN BOTH THE PEOPLE
AND INSTITUTIONS

06:53.147 --> 06:55.947
IN WHICH
THEY ONCE PLACED THEIR FAITH.

06:55.949 --> 06:57.147
LET'S DO OUR BEST

06:57.149 --> 07:01.419
TO NOT HASTEN THAT LOSS
OF INNOCENCE, SHALL WE?

07:02.855 --> 07:05.056
[♪]

07:09.996 --> 07:10.996
AHEM.

07:20.640 --> 07:22.707
"DEAR MRS. RICHARDS--
DO YOU REMEMBER ME?

07:22.709 --> 07:24.176
"I HOPE SO.

07:24.178 --> 07:25.977
"MY FAVOURITE COLOR IS PURPLE.

07:25.979 --> 07:29.681
"I HATE MATH,
IT MAKES MY HEAD HURT,

07:29.683 --> 07:31.550
"AND I LOVE STARS,

07:31.552 --> 07:34.820
BUT MORE THAN ANYTHING,
I LOVE FLOWERS."

07:36.155 --> 07:37.556
"HEY! YOU'RE MARRIED!"

07:37.558 --> 07:39.156
[CHUCKLES]

07:41.627 --> 07:44.596
<i>"YOU WERE A BEAUTIFUL BRIDE.</i>

07:44.598 --> 07:46.198
<i>"I KNOW THAT'S TRUE,</i>

07:46.200 --> 07:48.066
<i>"BECAUSE YOUR DAD TOLD YOU</i>

07:48.068 --> 07:49.901
<i>"THAT YOU WERE THE MOST BEAUTIFUL BRIDE</i>

07:49.903 --> 07:51.770
<i>"HE HAD EVER SEEN.</i>

07:51.772 --> 07:54.739
<i>"EVEN BOBBY SAID</i>

07:54.741 --> 07:58.043
THE FLOWERS IN YOUR HAIR
MADE YOU LOOK LIKE AN ANGEL."

07:58.045 --> 07:59.644
OKAY. I HAVE 2,037

07:59.646 --> 08:02.080
"ROBERT" OR "BOBBY RICHARDS"

08:02.082 --> 08:03.248
IN THE WESTERN STATES.

08:03.250 --> 08:04.950
DOESN'T REALLY
NARROW IT DOWN MUCH.

08:04.952 --> 08:07.486
"YOU'RE SO LUCKY TO HAVE BOBBY.

08:07.488 --> 08:09.621
HE IS SO-O-O-O HANDSOME."

08:10.723 --> 08:12.691
"I'LL BET ALL YOUR FRIENDS
ARE JEALOUS.

08:12.693 --> 08:14.259
"REMEMBER TO BE NICE TO BOBBY.

08:14.261 --> 08:15.961
<i>"DON'T BE BOSSY.</i>

08:15.963 --> 08:18.163
<i>"HE JUST WANTS TO TAKE CARE OF YOU.</i>

08:18.165 --> 08:22.267
"OH, AND I HOPE YOU'RE DANCING.
<i>UNDER THE STARS.</i>

08:22.269 --> 08:25.070
<i>"WITH FLOWERS FALLING DOWN.</i>

08:25.072 --> 08:28.607
BECAUSE WHEN I CLOSE MY EYES, THAT'S HOW I SEE YOU."

08:31.511 --> 08:33.178
"LOVE, ELLIE."

08:33.180 --> 08:36.548
OH, AND THERE'S A P.S.

08:36.550 --> 08:38.517
"IF I'M WRONG ABOUT WHAT I WROTE,

08:38.519 --> 08:40.652
"YOU HAVE TO CHANGE IT. NOW!

08:40.654 --> 08:42.621
"AND IF ANYONE TRIES TO STOP YOU,

08:42.623 --> 08:47.092
JUST SAY,
'NO! THIS IS MY LIFE!!'"

08:47.094 --> 08:48.960
THAT'S WITH TWO EXCLAMATION POINTS

08:48.962 --> 08:51.596
AND LOTS OF UNDERLINING.

08:51.598 --> 08:53.765
IF ONLY WE COULD MAKE THINGS TRUE

08:53.767 --> 08:56.701
BY UNDERLINING THEIR IMPORTANCE, HUH?

08:58.671 --> 09:00.872
THIS WASN'T PROPERLY PROCESSED, HMM?

09:00.874 --> 09:03.675
OH. UH, KIMMI BROUGHT IT IN PERSONALLY.

09:03.677 --> 09:05.644
THEN YOU SPEAK WITH KIMMI.

09:05.646 --> 09:06.745
PERSONALLY.

09:06.747 --> 09:09.247
[HUSHED]: OH. OKAY.

09:16.055 --> 09:17.989
"BOULDER JONES'  FURNITURE WAREHOUSE".

09:17.991 --> 09:19.624
5615 NORTH DRUMHELLER.

09:19.626 --> 09:20.792
GOT IT. THANKS.

09:20.794 --> 09:21.826
ANYTIME.

09:21.828 --> 09:23.562
UH, HEY. LOOK.

09:23.564 --> 09:27.132
I KNOW HOW THESE "MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY" TYPE PAGEANTS GO.

09:27.134 --> 09:28.934
REALLY?

09:28.936 --> 09:30.135
HOW'S THAT?

09:30.137 --> 09:31.903
OH, WELL, YOU KNOW,

09:31.905 --> 09:33.905
BACKSTABBING,
STEALING SECRETS,

09:33.907 --> 09:35.206
PRETENDING TO BE SOMEONE'S FRIEND

09:35.208 --> 09:36.741
JUST SO YOU CAN UNDERMINE THEM.

09:36.743 --> 09:38.577
WE'VE ALL BEEN THERE.

09:38.579 --> 09:39.844
IS THAT SO?

09:39.846 --> 09:42.347
AND WHAT KIND OF A PAGEANT
HAVE YOU BEEN IN?

09:42.349 --> 09:46.217
OH, WELL, IT WAS
A ROBOTICS COMPETITION.

09:47.620 --> 09:49.754
AHEM. BUT THE, UH, POLITICS
ARE ALL THE SAME.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.189
IF YOU SAY SO.

09:51.191 --> 09:52.290
I DO.

09:52.292 --> 09:53.892
SO DO YOURSELF A FAVOUR.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.226
DON'T MESS WITH RITA.

09:55.228 --> 09:56.361
[SNICKERS]

09:56.363 --> 09:57.796
"NEWSFLASH!"

09:57.798 --> 10:00.131
RITA IS NEAR-SIGHTED

10:00.133 --> 10:02.601
AND SHE DRESSES LIKE A REFUGEE FROM <i>LES MISERABLES.</i>

10:02.603 --> 10:05.103
SHE HASN'T EVEN DECLARED
A TALENT FOR THE TALENT SECTION

10:05.105 --> 10:08.173
'CAUSE I'M GUESSING THAT
SHE PROBABLY DOESN'T HAVE ONE.

10:08.175 --> 10:10.041
WHY WOULD I MESS WITH HER?

10:10.043 --> 10:12.010
SHE'S ALREADY LOST.

10:13.646 --> 10:16.047
[♪]

10:27.059 --> 10:29.060
AHEM.

10:29.062 --> 10:31.863
[♪]

10:31.865 --> 10:34.099
I WONDER
HOW NORMAN'S DOING

10:34.101 --> 10:36.401
AT THE FURNITURE STORE.

10:36.403 --> 10:38.637
IT'S HIS FIRST SOLO INVESTIGATION.

10:38.639 --> 10:41.006
I'M SURE HE'S FINE.

10:41.008 --> 10:42.807
JUST THOUGHT MAYBE IT'S TOO SOON.

10:42.809 --> 10:45.810
IT'S NEVER EASY TO PUSH
ONE'S PROTEGE OUT OF THE NEST,

10:45.812 --> 10:47.212
MS. McINERNEY,

10:47.214 --> 10:50.782
BUT NORMAN IS READY
TO SPREAD HIS WINGS A LITTLE,

10:50.784 --> 10:52.917
AND I THINK THIS IS
A GOOD TEST FLIGHT FOR HIM.

10:58.691 --> 11:00.058
[INHALES DEEPLY]

11:00.060 --> 11:01.993
OLIVER, IS EVERYTHING OKAY WITH US?

11:03.896 --> 11:05.697
US, MS. McINERNEY?

11:05.699 --> 11:08.233
WELL, MAYBE I'M JUST BEING SILLY, BUT, UM...

11:08.235 --> 11:10.769
YOU FEEL DISTANT TO ME.

11:10.771 --> 11:12.437
FROM ME.

11:12.439 --> 11:14.706
I'M RIGHT HERE.

11:14.708 --> 11:16.107
AS ARE YOU.

11:16.109 --> 11:18.209
UH...

11:18.211 --> 11:19.411
THERE'S NO DISTANCE.

11:21.247 --> 11:22.046
OKAY.

11:25.918 --> 11:27.085
OH, YOU HAVE  A LITTLE SOMETHING--

11:28.387 --> 11:30.422
[♪]

11:38.998 --> 11:41.032
RITA!

11:41.034 --> 11:43.168
OH!

11:44.303 --> 11:46.037
I'VE BEEN DOING SOME CHECKING AROUND.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.772
KIMMI IS A BRANCH-HOPPER.

11:47.774 --> 11:49.040
SHE GOES FROM BRANCH TO BRANCH,

11:49.042 --> 11:50.809
JUST TO AUDITION FOR "MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY".

11:50.811 --> 11:53.378
WOW!
SHE SOUNDS VERY GOAL-ORIENTED.

11:53.380 --> 11:54.446
I ADMIRE THAT.

11:54.448 --> 11:56.181
BUT SHE HAS UNDERESTIMATED YOU.

11:56.183 --> 11:59.718
YOU ARE GONNA GIVE HER A RUN FOR HER MONEY.

11:59.720 --> 12:01.753
YOU ARE GONNA BE CHOSEN TO REPRESENT THIS BRANCH,

12:01.755 --> 12:02.954
AND I'M GONNA HELP YOU.

12:02.956 --> 12:04.122
SO TELL ME

12:04.124 --> 12:05.757
BESIDES KIMMI,
WHO ELSE IS COMPETING?

12:05.759 --> 12:06.858
JUST ONE OTHER PERSON.

12:06.860 --> 12:08.126
UH, VIVINEE RUCKER?

12:08.128 --> 12:10.395
"RUCKER"?

12:10.397 --> 12:12.397
THE NEW SUPERVISOR'S NAME IS GLYNIS RUCKER.

12:13.866 --> 12:15.033
YOU DON'T SUPPOSE...?

12:15.035 --> 12:17.168
[♪]

12:17.170 --> 12:20.972
<i>ALL ROUTE TRANSFER REQUESTS</i>
<i>NOT RECEIVED BY 3:00 P.M.</i>

12:20.974 --> 12:23.274
WILL BE ROLLED INTO THE NEXT QUARTER.

12:23.276 --> 12:25.210
NO EXCEPTIONS.

12:25.212 --> 12:27.779
NONE.

12:27.781 --> 12:29.047
ZERO.

12:30.015 --> 12:31.916
THANK YOU.

12:33.152 --> 12:35.086
THAT'S RIGHT.

12:35.088 --> 12:36.387
VIVINEE'S MY BABY.

12:36.389 --> 12:38.757
SHE, UH, WORKS GRAVEYARD SHIFT, UP IN PROCESSING.

12:38.759 --> 12:41.826
SHE'S THINKING OF "MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY," HUH?

12:41.828 --> 12:43.962
OH! SHE'S MORE THAN THINKING!

12:43.964 --> 12:47.132
THIS HAS BEEN A DREAM OF HERS
SINCE SHE WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

12:47.134 --> 12:49.768
[BARKS]: BOB!
SPIT OUT THAT GUM!

12:51.003 --> 12:52.237
[GRUMBLING SIGH]

12:53.806 --> 12:55.974
KIDS GROW UP SO FAST.

12:55.976 --> 12:57.776
YEAH, JUST THE OTHER DAY,
I WAS ASKING HER

12:57.778 --> 13:00.145
IF I COULD HELP HER
WITH HER AUDITION AND, UH....

13:00.147 --> 13:02.046
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
THAT LITTLE GIRL SAID TO ME?

13:02.048 --> 13:03.815
MM?

13:03.817 --> 13:07.452
SHE SAID, "THAT'S OKAY, MOM.
I NEED TO DO THIS ON MY OWN."

13:07.454 --> 13:09.053
PRECIOUS.

13:09.055 --> 13:10.221
[SIGHS] YEAH.

13:10.223 --> 13:12.924
YEAH, I'D DO ANYTHING
FOR MY DAUGHTER.

13:12.926 --> 13:14.926
ANYTHING.

13:16.462 --> 13:19.364
[♪]

13:19.366 --> 13:22.000
OH, HOLD ON, NORMAN.
MS. McINERNEY JUST ARRIVED.

13:22.002 --> 13:23.968
PERHAPS IT'D BE BEST
IF YOU TOLD HER YOURSELF.

13:23.970 --> 13:26.971
OH, AND NORMAN, GOOD WORK.
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

13:30.109 --> 13:32.210
WHAT DO YOU
GOT FOR ME, NORMAN?

13:32.212 --> 13:34.112
[NORMAN]: <i>BILL OF SALE</i>
<i>SAYS THE DESK WAS SOLD</i>

13:34.114 --> 13:35.413
AT AN AUCTION SIX YEARS AGO

13:35.415 --> 13:37.182
BY THE LONGMONT, COLORADO,
SCHOOL DISTRICT.

13:37.184 --> 13:38.983
GREAT. SO,
IF WE CAN NARROW IT DOWN

13:38.985 --> 13:40.118
TO A SPECIFIC CLASSROOM

13:40.120 --> 13:41.419
AND TEACHER--

13:41.421 --> 13:43.388
ALREADY DONE.
WELL, THE FIRST PART, ANYWAYS.

13:43.390 --> 13:46.057
THERE'S A METAL PLATE
ON THE DESK

13:46.059 --> 13:49.594
THAT READS,
"LONGMONT, 145, R.M.H.S."

13:49.596 --> 13:52.397
"R.M.H.S."

13:52.399 --> 13:54.132
"ROCKY MOUNTAIN HIGH SCHOOL."

13:54.134 --> 13:55.366
CLASSROOM NUMBER 145.

13:55.368 --> 13:57.268
NORMAN, YOU'RE MY HERO.

14:00.573 --> 14:02.207
-[CLASS BELL RINGS]
-LET'S SEE.

14:02.209 --> 14:05.910
SIX YEARS AGO,
THIS CLASSROOM WAS...

14:05.912 --> 14:08.279
MS. HINKLE'S.
ENGLISH LITERATURE.

14:08.281 --> 14:09.547
CAN WE SPEAK
WITH HER, PLEASE?

14:09.549 --> 14:11.149
OH, SHE RETIRED.

14:11.151 --> 14:14.085
THE LETTER WAS INTENDED
FOR A "MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS".

14:14.087 --> 14:16.120
PERHAPS YOU COULD TELL US
IF ANYONE BY THAT NAME

14:16.122 --> 14:18.857
HAS BEEN EMPLOYED
BY THE SCHOOL DISTRICT?

14:18.859 --> 14:21.359
NO. NO ONE BY THAT NAME.

14:21.361 --> 14:24.629
WELL, WE MAY HAVE
ERRED, MS. McINERNEY.

14:24.631 --> 14:26.097
MADE ASSUMPTIONS
WE SHOULDN'T HAVE.

14:26.099 --> 14:27.966
LIKE WHAT?

14:27.968 --> 14:30.301
OH, THAT, UH, ELLIE EVER
WENT TO SCHOOL HERE.

14:30.303 --> 14:31.603
WE'RE IN
A HIGH SCHOOL CLASSROOM.

14:31.605 --> 14:33.471
THE PENMANSHIP
OF THE LETTER

14:33.473 --> 14:36.174
CLEARLY INDICATES
A MUCH YOUNGER WRITER.

14:36.176 --> 14:40.345
IT MIGHT BE TIME
TO ADMIT DEFEAT AND MOVE ON.

14:45.317 --> 14:47.418
OLIVER.

14:47.420 --> 14:50.955
THE DESK WE TRACED
WAS IN THAT CLASSROOM.

14:50.957 --> 14:52.924
THE LETTER
WAS IN THAT DESK.

14:52.926 --> 14:55.927
THIS IS MOST DEFINITELY
NOT THE TIME TO ADMIT DEFEAT.

14:57.096 --> 15:00.064
IT MUST BE NICE TO POSSESS
SUCH CERTAINTY.

15:00.066 --> 15:02.066
YOU KNOW,
IT JUST OCCURRED TO ME--

15:02.068 --> 15:03.234
WE HAD A STUDENT,

15:03.236 --> 15:05.336
HE GRADUATED
ABOUT FIVE YEARS AGO.

15:05.338 --> 15:07.005
HIS NAME WAS BOBBY RICHARDS.

15:07.007 --> 15:08.506
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE WE CAN FIND HIM?

15:08.508 --> 15:10.174
I DO, ACTUALLY.

15:13.612 --> 15:15.046
RITA, DEAR...

15:15.048 --> 15:16.381
OH--

15:16.383 --> 15:17.682
[SIGHS] OH,
MY BABY GIRL

15:17.684 --> 15:20.285
REALLY WANTS TO BE
MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY.

15:20.287 --> 15:21.986
OH, WELL,
I COULDN'T IMAGINE

15:21.988 --> 15:23.354
ANYONE WHO WOULDN'T
WANT TO BE

15:23.356 --> 15:24.956
MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY.

15:24.958 --> 15:26.958
YES, BUT
MY VIVINEE, OOH...

15:26.960 --> 15:29.160
SHE WANTS IT
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

15:29.162 --> 15:32.697
IT WOULD JUST KILL ME
TO SEE HER DISAPPOINTED.

15:32.699 --> 15:34.198
[CHUCKLES]

15:34.200 --> 15:35.533
SO.

15:35.535 --> 15:39.337
IF EITHER YOU,
OR THAT BIG SNOOP SHANE,

15:39.339 --> 15:43.041
GETS IN THE WAY OF MY BABY
HAVING WHAT SHE WANTS...

15:44.310 --> 15:46.978
I'M GONNA SQUASH YOU
LIKE A BUG.

15:53.419 --> 15:55.520
DO HAVE A NICE DAY NOW.

15:56.655 --> 15:59.123
[♪]

16:04.129 --> 16:06.331
WELL, ELLIE WROTE
IN THE LETTER

16:06.333 --> 16:09.133
THAT SHE HOPES MRS. RICHARDS
LOVES FLOWERS,

16:09.135 --> 16:10.368
AND HERE WE ARE,
IN A FLOWER SHOP.

16:10.370 --> 16:12.704
MORE THAN
A COINCIDENCE?

16:12.706 --> 16:14.472
OR JUST GOOD
DETECTIVE WORK.

16:15.708 --> 16:17.342
[DING]

16:19.345 --> 16:20.311
HELLO!

16:20.313 --> 16:22.080
HI!

16:22.082 --> 16:24.282
I'M BOBBY.
WELCOME TO "BLOOMS'N'HUGS".

16:24.284 --> 16:26.317
THESE ARE THE BLOOMS...

16:26.319 --> 16:27.618
AND THESE ARE THE HUGS.

16:27.620 --> 16:29.320
OH!

16:32.458 --> 16:34.058
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

16:34.060 --> 16:35.360
ARE YOU
BOBBY RICHARDS?

16:35.362 --> 16:36.627
YES.

16:36.629 --> 16:38.296
AND THIS
IS YOUR SHOP?

16:38.298 --> 16:42.433
WHY? YOU HAVE A PROBLEM WITH
A GUY OWNING A FLOWER SHOP?

16:42.435 --> 16:44.502
NO. NO!
NOT AT ALL.

16:44.504 --> 16:46.204
ACTUALLY,
MY MOM AND DAD OWN IT,

16:46.206 --> 16:47.305
BUT I'M THE FLOWER GUY.

16:47.307 --> 16:48.606
DO YOU NEED FLOWERS?

16:48.608 --> 16:51.376
OH, UH, MR. RICHARDS,
I AM OLIVER O'TOOLE.

16:51.378 --> 16:53.411
THIS IS MY COLLEAGUE,
MS. McINERNEY.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.747
WE'RE FROM THE UNITED
STATES POSTAL SERVICE

16:55.749 --> 16:57.115
AND WE HAVE
A LETTER TO DELIVER

16:57.117 --> 16:58.616
TO A "MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS".

16:58.618 --> 17:00.718
IS THAT YOUR WIFE?

17:00.720 --> 17:02.420
OR MOTHER, PERHAPS?

17:02.422 --> 17:04.555
WELL, I'M NOT MARRIED,

17:04.557 --> 17:07.792
AND MY MOM'S NAME
IS MRS. PAUL RICHARDS.

17:07.794 --> 17:09.127
IS THAT THE LETTER?

17:09.129 --> 17:11.796
YES. YES, IT IS.

17:11.798 --> 17:14.332
ELLIE? CAN YOU COME
OUT HERE FOR A SECOND?

17:14.334 --> 17:15.333
ELLIE?

17:15.335 --> 17:16.501
UH...

17:16.503 --> 17:18.369
THAT'S--
THAT'S WHO WROTE THIS LETTER.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.471
I KNOW!
I RECOGNIZE THE HANDWRITING.

17:20.473 --> 17:21.439
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO READ.

17:21.441 --> 17:23.307
ELLIE?

17:23.309 --> 17:24.776
YEAH? WHAT'S UP?

17:24.778 --> 17:26.411
UM...

17:26.413 --> 17:30.715
THESE PEOPLE WANT TO ASK YOU
ABOUT A LETTER YOU WROTE.

17:30.717 --> 17:32.116
MY LETTER!

17:32.118 --> 17:33.317
YOU HAVE MY LETTER!

17:33.319 --> 17:36.487
UH, UNFORTUNATELY, ELLIE,

17:36.489 --> 17:38.556
ALTHOUGH YOU WROTE THE LETTER,
WE HAVE TO TRY AND DELIVER THIS

17:38.558 --> 17:40.291
TO A "MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS".

17:40.293 --> 17:42.527
[SHANE]: DO YOU KNOW
WHERE WE COULD FIND HER?

17:43.629 --> 17:45.730
THIS IS SO EMBARRASSING.

17:48.200 --> 17:49.600
[TAKES A BREATH, SIGHS]

17:49.602 --> 17:52.403
I'M "MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS".

17:52.405 --> 17:54.138
BUT...

17:54.140 --> 17:56.207
THE TWO OF YOU
AREN'T MARRIED, RIGHT?

17:56.209 --> 17:58.476
OR A-- ARE YOU?

17:58.478 --> 18:00.244
IT'S COMPLICATED.

18:00.246 --> 18:01.612
[BOBBY CHUCKLES]:
IT'S...

18:01.614 --> 18:03.514
COMPLICATED.

18:03.516 --> 18:05.316
SO, WHEN DID YOU

18:05.318 --> 18:08.686
BECOME MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS
WITHOUT TELLING ME?

18:08.688 --> 18:10.188
SINCE THE FUTURE.

18:10.190 --> 18:14.392
MRS. BOBBY RICHARDS
IS WHO I AM IN OUR FUTURE.

18:14.394 --> 18:16.661
IT WILL BE OUR FUTURE,

18:16.663 --> 18:20.264
BUT NOT UNTIL YOUR MOM
AND DAD SAY IT'S OKAY.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.200
MAY I SEE
THE LETTER, PLEASE?

18:22.202 --> 18:23.534
OH, SURE. UM...

18:23.536 --> 18:25.103
I APOLOGIZE
FOR IT BEING LATE.

18:25.105 --> 18:26.838
WHEN WERE YOU
SUPPOSED TO GET IT?

18:26.840 --> 18:29.540
I THINK MS. HINKLE SAID
10 YEARS...

18:29.542 --> 18:31.275
SEVEN YEARS AGO.

18:31.277 --> 18:33.244
SO THAT WOULD BE...

18:35.447 --> 18:39.350
SO THE ASSIGNMENT IS TO WRITE
A LETTER TO YOUR FUTURE SELF.

18:42.821 --> 18:45.556
WHERE DO YOU WANT TO BE
10 YEARS FROM NOW?

18:45.558 --> 18:47.225
WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO BE DOING?

18:47.227 --> 18:49.127
WHO DO YOU WANT TO BE WITH?

18:49.129 --> 18:50.862
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

18:50.864 --> 18:52.530
SEE YOURSELF THERE.

18:52.532 --> 18:55.566
AND WRITE A LETTER
TO <i>THAT PERSON.</i>

18:55.568 --> 18:57.401
PUT YOUR LETTER IN THE ENVELOPE
AND ADDRESS IT,

18:57.403 --> 18:59.770
AND GIVE IT BACK TO ME
AT THE END OF THE PERIOD,

18:59.772 --> 19:02.240
AND I PROMISE TO MAIL THEM
BACK TO YOU IN 10 YEARS.

19:02.242 --> 19:04.475
SO WHEN YOU OPEN YOUR LETTER
IN 2017,

19:04.477 --> 19:05.910
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO COMPARE

19:05.912 --> 19:08.513
WHERE YOU ARE
TO WHERE YOU THOUGHT YOU'D BE.

19:08.515 --> 19:11.415
AND IF YOU'RE NOT
WHERE YOU THOUGHT YOU'D BE...

19:11.417 --> 19:12.884
MAYBE THIS LETTER'S

19:12.886 --> 19:14.519
THE KICK IN THE PANTS
YOU'LL NEED.

19:14.521 --> 19:16.387
[CLASS LAUGHING]

19:18.624 --> 19:20.491
[ELLIE'S VOICE]:
<i>DEAR... MRS. RICHARDS...</i>

19:20.493 --> 19:22.693
<i>DO YOU REMEMBER ME?</i>

19:22.695 --> 19:24.662
"I HOPE SO."

19:24.664 --> 19:27.465
"REMEMBER TO BE NICE TO BOBBY.
DON'T BE BOSSY."

19:27.467 --> 19:29.167
[PLAYFULLY]: MM!

19:29.169 --> 19:30.601
"HE JUST WANTS TO TAKE CARE OF YOU."

19:30.603 --> 19:32.470
THAT'S TRUE. I DO.

19:32.472 --> 19:34.238
-[ALL CHUCKLING]
-KEEP READING!

19:34.240 --> 19:35.406
I WANT TO HEAR SOME MORE.

19:35.408 --> 19:37.475
IT'S JUST MUSHY STUFF.
BLAH-BLAH-BLAH.

19:37.477 --> 19:39.443
"LOVE, ELLIE."

19:39.445 --> 19:41.579
"AND P.S., IF I'M WRONG

19:41.581 --> 19:43.581
ABOUT WHAT I WROTE..."

19:48.720 --> 19:50.354
YOU HAVE TO
TAKE ME HOME, BOBBY!

19:50.356 --> 19:52.557
I HAVE TO DO SOMETHING.
RIGHT NOW.

19:52.559 --> 19:54.258
ELLIE, I CAN'T, I GOTTA WORK.
I HAVE DELIVERIES.

19:54.260 --> 19:56.360
YOU CAN BE
SO FRUSTRATING SOMETIMES!

19:56.362 --> 19:57.361
WE COULD TAKE YOU.

19:59.431 --> 20:01.365
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
MR. O'TOOLE?

20:01.367 --> 20:02.567
[WHISPERS]: YEAH.

20:06.638 --> 20:07.772
MR. KEMPERT?

20:07.774 --> 20:09.340
HI. I'M SHANE.

20:09.342 --> 20:10.541
WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE.

20:10.543 --> 20:12.610
DAD, WE HAVE
TO TALK. NOW.

20:12.612 --> 20:14.645
[MR. KEMPERT]: OKAY.
LET'S START WITH

20:14.647 --> 20:16.414
WHY YOU ASKED THESE PEOPLE
TO BRING YOU HOME.

20:16.416 --> 20:18.950
BECAUSE THEY BROUGHT ME
MY LETTER BACK.

20:18.952 --> 20:20.551
SIR, I'M OLIVER O'TOOLE

20:20.553 --> 20:21.686
FROM THE UNITED STATES
POSTAL SERVICE--

20:21.688 --> 20:23.554
I WROTE IT
AND I HAVE TO MARRY BOBBY.

20:23.556 --> 20:25.389
WELL, UM... CAN I SEE IT?

20:25.391 --> 20:27.658
NO! CAN I MARRY BOBBY OR NOT?

20:27.660 --> 20:29.293
HIS PARENTS SAY
IT'S OKAY.

20:29.295 --> 20:30.861
OKAY, ELLIE, LOOK.

20:30.863 --> 20:31.896
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT THIS,
AND--

20:31.898 --> 20:33.998
MOM! I WANT TO GET MARRIED!

20:34.000 --> 20:37.368
I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT ANYMORE!

20:37.370 --> 20:40.538
AND IT HURTS WHEN YOU TALK TO ME
LIKE I'M A BABY.

20:40.540 --> 20:43.307
LOOK, I'M SORRY, ELLIE,
BUT PLEASE, COULD WE GO INSIDE--

20:43.309 --> 20:44.475
NO!

20:44.477 --> 20:45.910
THIS IS MY LIFE!

20:45.912 --> 20:47.511
MY LIFE!

20:47.513 --> 20:48.946
I'M GETTING MARRIED,

20:48.948 --> 20:51.349
AND YOU CAN'T STOP ME!

20:52.918 --> 20:55.586
[♪]

20:59.891 --> 21:01.626
THANK YOU
FOR BRINGING HER HOME.

21:01.628 --> 21:03.728
I APPRECIATE IT.

21:03.730 --> 21:05.463
IT MIGHT NOT BE MY PLACE--

21:05.465 --> 21:07.999
MS. McINERNEY,
DO YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

21:09.268 --> 21:11.869
NO. I DON'T.

21:13.472 --> 21:15.940
THANKS FOR CARING, THOUGH.

21:17.709 --> 21:19.677
[SHANE SIGHS]

21:21.613 --> 21:23.381
PLEASE KEEP IN MIND,
MS. McINERNEY--

21:23.383 --> 21:24.882
ALTHOUGH I HAVE LEARNED
TO INDULGE YOUR HABIT

21:24.884 --> 21:26.450
OF INSERTING YOURSELF
INTO PEOPLE'S LIVES,

21:26.452 --> 21:27.885
OTHERS WHO
DO NOT KNOW YOU

21:27.887 --> 21:30.288
MAY NOT.

21:30.290 --> 21:32.456
WE DID OUR JOB.
WE DELIVERED THE LETTER.

21:32.458 --> 21:35.926
[♪]

21:39.531 --> 21:40.698
[MAN]: HELLO. GOOD EVENING.
HERE'S MY FIRST SONG.

21:42.301 --> 21:44.035
[PLAYS GUITAR]

21:47.406 --> 21:48.706
THANK YOU, EVERYBODY.
THANK YOU.

21:48.708 --> 21:50.341
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT
MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY--

21:50.343 --> 21:51.876
YOU'RE AUDITIONING, TOO?

21:51.878 --> 21:54.645
NO, RITA.
I WANT TO HELP YOU.

21:54.647 --> 21:56.380
-OH!
-YOU NEED A STRATEGY.

21:56.382 --> 21:59.417
LET'S BEGIN WITH
AN HONEST SELF-APPRAISAL--

21:59.419 --> 22:02.019
ASSESS YOUR STRENGTHS
AND WEAKNESSES.

22:02.021 --> 22:04.588
HOW WOULD YOU RATE YOUR SORTING
SKILLS FOR THE COMPULSORIES?

22:04.590 --> 22:06.457
PRETTY GOOD, I THINK.

22:06.459 --> 22:07.758
OKAY. GREAT.

22:07.760 --> 22:09.493
'CAUSE YOU'RE KIND OF
ON YOUR OWN WITH THAT.

22:09.495 --> 22:10.661
SORTING IS MORE YOUR THING.

22:10.663 --> 22:12.596
WHAT ABOUT
POISE AND APPEARANCE?

22:12.598 --> 22:14.999
WELL, THE JUDGES
ASK EACH OF US A QUESTION,

22:15.001 --> 22:16.967
BUT WE DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS
UNTIL WE GET THERE.

22:16.969 --> 22:18.669
MY ADVICE ON THAT
IS KEEP YOUR ANSWER SHORT.

22:18.671 --> 22:21.806
DON'T THINK, OR TALK...

22:21.808 --> 22:24.041
OR THINK TOO MUCH.

22:25.477 --> 22:27.812
[♪]

22:31.083 --> 22:32.516
IS SOMEONE HELPING YOU
WITH YOUR HAIR AND MAKEUP?

22:32.518 --> 22:34.385
I NEED HAIR AND MAKEUP?

22:34.387 --> 22:36.620
MOVING ON TO TALENT.

22:36.622 --> 22:38.489
-OKAY...
-WHAT IS IT?

22:38.491 --> 22:40.591
OH. WELL, I FINALLY
TOOK NORMAN'S ADVICE,

22:40.593 --> 22:42.660
AND I MEMORIZED
THE 2014 POSTAL CODE.

22:42.662 --> 22:44.028
GO AHEAD.
ASK ME ANYTHING.

22:44.030 --> 22:46.430
PAGE... 396?

22:46.432 --> 22:48.899
"OKAY. SECTION FOUR,

22:48.901 --> 22:50.468
"SUBSECTION 56--

22:50.470 --> 22:52.436
"DELIVERIES
GOING TO CARNIVALS, CIRCUSES,

22:52.438 --> 22:53.838
"OR TRANSIENT ATTRACTIONS:

22:53.840 --> 22:55.039
ALL LETTERS SHOULD--"

22:55.041 --> 22:56.540
OKAY, GOT IT!

22:56.542 --> 22:57.808
GOOD. THAT SHOULD
BE ENOUGH TO BEAT

22:57.810 --> 22:59.510
OLD "TUBA-LIPS" KIMMI.

22:59.512 --> 23:02.913
NOW, THE ONLY
QUESTION MARK IS VIVINEE.

23:02.915 --> 23:07.051
[WOMAN SINGING]:
♪ ...FOR ME AND MY GAL

23:07.053 --> 23:09.019
-♪ THE BIRDS ARE...
-WHO'S THAT?

23:09.021 --> 23:10.588
♪ SINGING
FOR ME AND MY GAL ♪

23:10.590 --> 23:12.757
[RITA]: WOW...
SHE'S REALLY GOOD.

23:12.759 --> 23:13.991
LADIES.

23:13.993 --> 23:16.894
HOW DO YOU LIKE
MY BABY'S SINGING?

23:16.896 --> 23:19.897
♪ ...KNOWIN'
TO A WEDDIN' THEY'RE-- ♪

23:19.899 --> 23:21.098
THAT'S VIVINEE?

23:21.100 --> 23:22.867
SURE IS.

23:22.869 --> 23:24.769
SEE YOU AROUND.

23:25.837 --> 23:29.507
♪ EVERY SUZIE AND SAL

23:29.509 --> 23:33.477
[TOGETHER]:
♪ THEY'RE CONGREGATIN'

23:33.479 --> 23:36.847
♪ FOR ME AND MY GAL

23:36.849 --> 23:38.015
[DEFEATED SIGH] UH...

23:38.017 --> 23:39.784
LET'S TALK SOME MORE

23:39.786 --> 23:41.652
ABOUT POISE
AND APPEARANCE, SHALL WE?

23:41.654 --> 23:44.922
♪ FOR ME AND MY GAL

23:44.924 --> 23:48.058
[♪]

23:48.060 --> 23:50.027
GENTLEMEN,
IT IS MY DISTINCT PRIVILEGE

23:50.029 --> 23:52.430
AND PLEASURE
TO PRESENT TO YOU

23:52.432 --> 23:53.831
THE NEXT...

23:53.833 --> 23:54.932
MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY...

23:54.934 --> 23:56.967
MISS...

23:56.969 --> 23:58.502
RITA HAYWITH!

24:04.743 --> 24:07.745
[♪]

24:17.756 --> 24:20.524
[♪]

24:29.468 --> 24:31.235
POSTURE.

24:34.573 --> 24:36.707
WELL? AREN'T YOU
GOING TO SAY SOMETHING?

24:38.577 --> 24:41.512
RITA, UH,
THERE IS... AHEM,

24:41.514 --> 24:43.180
INDEED A REASON

24:43.182 --> 24:46.484
FOR OUR PROLONGED
SILENCE.

24:46.486 --> 24:47.618
YOU HAVE, IN FACT,

24:47.620 --> 24:50.054
TAKEN OUR BREATH AWAY.

24:50.056 --> 24:51.489
[GASPS]

24:51.491 --> 24:53.023
THANK YOU, OLIVER.

24:53.025 --> 24:54.925
[SHANE]:
WE DID A LITTLE HAIR THING...

24:54.927 --> 24:56.694
A LITTLE MAKE-UP THING.

24:56.696 --> 24:58.562
A LITTLE EVERYTHING.

24:58.564 --> 25:00.531
WHAT DO YOU THINK, NORMAN?

25:00.533 --> 25:02.766
[♪]

25:07.038 --> 25:09.974
[FAN WHOOSHING]

25:11.943 --> 25:13.944
I THINK YOU LOOK LIKE
A DIFFERENT PERSON.

25:15.580 --> 25:17.581
[WHISPERS]: I KNOW.

25:18.817 --> 25:20.184
BUT I'M NOT.

25:20.186 --> 25:22.586
-OH.
-[CHUCKLING]

25:26.758 --> 25:28.092
MR. GARRETT,
THANK YOU AGAIN

25:28.094 --> 25:30.561
FOR THOSE PACKETS
TRANSFERS.

25:31.897 --> 25:33.564
-OLIVER?
-HMM?

25:33.566 --> 25:35.599
I KNOW YESTERDAY
YOU SAID

25:35.601 --> 25:37.101
ONCE WE DELIVER
ELLIE'S LETTER,

25:37.103 --> 25:38.235
OUR JOB IS DONE.

25:38.237 --> 25:40.304
IT'S REALLY NOT.

25:40.306 --> 25:42.806
I SUPPOSE THAT ARGUMENT
COULD BE MADE,

25:42.808 --> 25:43.974
BUT IT'S A MOOT POINT NOW.

25:43.976 --> 25:46.043
ACTUALLY, NOT SO MOOT.

25:47.646 --> 25:49.747
MR. O'TOOLE.
MS. McINERNEY.

25:49.749 --> 25:51.682
-MR. KEMPERT.
-IT'S ELLIE.

25:51.684 --> 25:54.084
SHE'S GONE. SO IS BOBBY.

25:54.086 --> 25:56.053
I THINK THEY'VE RUN OFF
TO GET MARRIED.

25:56.055 --> 25:56.987
WHAT CAN WE DO
TO HELP?

25:56.989 --> 25:58.255
I NEED TO KNOW

25:58.257 --> 25:59.555
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
IN THAT LETTER

25:59.557 --> 26:00.925
THAT COULD TELL US
WHERE THEY COULD'VE GONE.

26:00.927 --> 26:03.994
ANY CHANCE
YOU REMEMBER ANY OF IT?

26:03.996 --> 26:06.297
"AND I HOPE...

26:06.299 --> 26:08.265
"THAT YOU'RE DANCING,

26:08.267 --> 26:10.067
"UNDER THE STARS,

26:10.069 --> 26:12.002
"WITH FLOWERS FALLING DOWN.

26:12.004 --> 26:15.005
"'CAUSE WHEN I CLOSE MY EYES...

26:15.007 --> 26:16.907
THAT'S HOW I SEE YOU."

26:18.009 --> 26:19.910
THAT WAS OUR WEDDING.

26:19.912 --> 26:21.679
ELLIE'S MOM AND I
GOT MARRIED

26:21.681 --> 26:23.280
IN THIS BEAUTIFUL
RESTORED BARN,

26:23.282 --> 26:24.748
UP IN ELDORA.

26:24.750 --> 26:26.216
IT WAS THE SAME PLACE
WHERE ELLIE'S GRANDPARENTS

26:26.218 --> 26:28.185
GOT MARRIED.

26:28.187 --> 26:30.120
IT HAD LIGHTS
HANGING FROM THE RAFTERS.

26:30.122 --> 26:32.656
AS WE DANCED,
OUR GUESTS THREW FLOWERS.

26:32.658 --> 26:36.193
ELLIE, SHE THOUGHT
IT SOUNDED MAGICAL.

26:36.195 --> 26:37.795
IF ELLIE WANTED A WEDDING
JUST LIKE YOURS,

26:37.797 --> 26:39.363
WITH LIGHTS
AND FLOWERS...

26:39.365 --> 26:40.931
THEN MAYBE--

26:42.233 --> 26:44.268
IS THERE SOMEONE WE CAN CALL
TO SEE IF SHE'S UP THERE?

26:44.270 --> 26:46.737
NO. IT'S JUST AN OLD BARN.

26:46.739 --> 26:48.639
THERE'S NO RECORD OF
A MARRIAGE LICENSE

26:48.641 --> 26:49.707
BEING GRANTED,

26:49.709 --> 26:50.841
BUT IF THEY JUST SUBMITTED IT,

26:50.843 --> 26:52.341
IT WOULDN'T BE
IN THE SYSTEM YET.

26:52.343 --> 26:54.345
WELL, RITA AND I CAN
GO TO CITY HALL AND CHECK.

26:54.347 --> 26:55.913
I'M GONNA DRIVE UP TO THE BARN.

27:11.663 --> 27:13.330
[♪]

27:13.332 --> 27:14.398
OKAY.

27:14.400 --> 27:16.367
FOLLOW MY LEAD.

27:18.803 --> 27:20.237
EXCUSE ME.

27:20.239 --> 27:22.940
MY FIANCEE AND I WOULD
LIKE TO GET MARRIED.

27:24.242 --> 27:25.643
-REALLY?
-YES!

27:25.645 --> 27:26.343
WE WOULD.

27:26.345 --> 27:27.378
AND WE'D LIKE TO KNOW

27:27.380 --> 27:28.746
IF THIS IS
THE CORRECT PLACE

27:28.748 --> 27:30.648
TO OBTAIN
A MARRIAGE LICENSE.

27:30.650 --> 27:32.383
DON'T WE?

27:33.718 --> 27:35.419
SO THIS YOUNG LADY
IS YOUR FIANCEE?

27:38.323 --> 27:40.824
YES... I AM.

27:43.762 --> 27:45.696
YOU'RE...
UH, YOU'RE A LUCKY MAN.

27:45.698 --> 27:47.798
NO, NO,
I'M THE LUCKY ONE.

27:47.800 --> 27:51.135
WELL, YOU KNOW,
LUCK IS A FUNNY THING--

27:51.137 --> 27:54.004
SO... FILL THESE OUT
AND BRING THEM BACK.

27:54.006 --> 27:55.305
UH, THE THING IS,

27:55.307 --> 27:58.342
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO MEET
ANOTHER COUPLE HERE--

27:58.344 --> 28:01.311
BOBBY RICHARDS
AND ELLIE KEMPERT.

28:01.313 --> 28:04.348
COULD YOU TELL US
IF THEY'VE BEEN HERE YET?

28:04.350 --> 28:05.849
A DOUBLE WEDDING?

28:05.851 --> 28:08.352
UH... Y-YEAH.

28:08.354 --> 28:09.920
DOUBLE TROUBLE!

28:09.922 --> 28:11.922
[BOTH GIGGLING]

28:14.025 --> 28:15.459
ELLIE?

28:15.461 --> 28:17.828
ELLIE?

28:17.830 --> 28:19.963
THIS IS IT.

28:19.965 --> 28:22.833
THIS IS WHERE LESLIE AND I
GOT MARRIED, RIGHT HERE.

28:22.835 --> 28:25.035
MAYBE I'M WRONG.

28:25.037 --> 28:27.137
MAYBE THEY DIDN'T
COME HERE TO GET MARRIED.

28:27.139 --> 28:28.372
[PHONE RINGS]

28:28.374 --> 28:30.774
EXCUSE ME. HELLO?

28:30.776 --> 28:32.743
OH, HEY, NORMAN.
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

28:34.045 --> 28:35.813
OKAY.
OKAY, GREAT. THANKS.

28:36.981 --> 28:38.782
THEY DID GET
A MARRIAGE LICENSE.

28:38.784 --> 28:40.217
[SIGHS]

28:45.223 --> 28:48.392
WELL, YOU BOTH MUST THINK
I'M A HORRIBLE FATHER.

28:50.462 --> 28:53.797
WE'RE IN NO POSITION
TO JUDGE, MR. KEMPERT.

28:53.799 --> 28:56.100
WELL, THAT'S KIND
OF YOU TO SAY.

28:58.236 --> 28:59.203
WHAT'S THAT?

29:00.238 --> 29:02.406
THAT'S A YOKE.

29:02.408 --> 29:04.475
IT'S, UH, LIKE A HARNESS

29:04.477 --> 29:06.744
THAT JOINS OXEN
OR HORSES TOGETHER.

29:06.746 --> 29:08.145
IT EQUALIZES THE WEIGHT

29:08.147 --> 29:09.980
WHEN THEY'RE PULLING A PLOW
OR ANY KIND OF HEAVY LOAD.

29:09.982 --> 29:11.515
OH...

29:11.517 --> 29:13.383
WELL, I DON'T KNOW MUCH
ABOUT FARMING.

29:14.819 --> 29:16.420
OR PARENTING, IT SEEMS.

29:16.422 --> 29:18.822
WELL, YOU LEARN AS YOU GO.

29:20.024 --> 29:21.759
BEFORE ELLIE WAS BORN,

29:21.761 --> 29:23.193
THE DOCTOR TOLD US
THAT WE WERE GONNA HAVE

29:23.195 --> 29:24.862
A CHILD
WITH DOWN SYNDROME.

29:24.864 --> 29:26.029
YOU KNOW WHAT
MY THOUGHT WAS?

29:27.398 --> 29:28.899
"RUN."

29:28.901 --> 29:30.834
"GET AWAY."

29:31.936 --> 29:33.170
YOU WERE SCARED.

29:33.172 --> 29:34.438
AND YOU DIDN'T RUN.

29:34.440 --> 29:36.006
NO.

29:36.008 --> 29:38.475
I THANK GOD EVERY DAY
I DIDN'T.

29:40.044 --> 29:42.513
ELLIE'S THE MOST PRECIOUS,
WONDERFUL DAUGHTER IN THE WORLD.

29:42.515 --> 29:44.948
NOT A BURDEN,
A GIFT.

29:44.950 --> 29:45.949
MR. KEMPERT...

29:47.452 --> 29:49.019
I MAY BE THE LAST PERSON

29:49.021 --> 29:50.287
TO CONSIDER MYSELF

29:50.289 --> 29:53.056
AN EXPERT ON WHAT TRUE LOVE
LOOKS LIKE, BUT...

29:53.058 --> 29:54.558
WITH BOBBY,

29:54.560 --> 29:56.393
I SEE

29:56.395 --> 29:59.930
PATIENCE AND SENSITIVITY...

29:59.932 --> 30:02.399
A GENTLE SENSE OF HUMOR,

30:02.401 --> 30:05.536
AND THIS PROTECTIVE
KIND OF WISDOM...

30:05.538 --> 30:08.972
ALL THE QUALITIES I'D IMAGINE
THAT A FATHER WOULD WANT

30:08.974 --> 30:10.374
IN A SON-IN-LAW.

30:10.376 --> 30:12.843
[PHONE VIBRATING]

30:15.847 --> 30:17.447
IT'S MY WIFE.

30:17.449 --> 30:19.016
SHE'S FOUND HER.

30:19.018 --> 30:20.184
[RELIEVED SIGH]

30:24.422 --> 30:26.190
ELLIE.

30:26.192 --> 30:27.825
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

30:32.130 --> 30:34.364
I HAVE BEEN UP IN ELDORA,

30:34.366 --> 30:35.999
WAITING AND WAITING FOR YOU
AT THAT BARN.

30:36.001 --> 30:37.067
I'VE BEEN WORRIED SICK
ABOUT YOU.

30:37.069 --> 30:39.169
WHAT WERE YOU
DOING AT THE BARN?

30:39.171 --> 30:41.538
WELL, ISN'T THAT WHERE
YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED TONIGHT?

30:41.540 --> 30:43.207
YEAH. BUT NOT TONIGHT.

30:43.209 --> 30:45.042
NOT WITHOUT YOU!

30:45.044 --> 30:47.010
WELL, THEN WHY DID YOU--?

30:47.012 --> 30:48.378
THERE'S
NO WEDDING DATE

30:48.380 --> 30:50.280
ON THE LICENSE, MARK--
IT'S GOOD FOR 30 DAYS.

30:50.282 --> 30:52.549
THEY JUST WANTED
TO SHOW US THEY'RE SERIOUS.

30:52.551 --> 30:54.418
WE ARE SERIOUS.

30:54.420 --> 30:56.253
SO AM I.
I'M VERY SERIOUS.

30:56.255 --> 30:57.988
YOU ARE NOT READY
TO GET MARRIED, ELLIE.

30:57.990 --> 30:59.590
-NOT TONIGHT, NOT IN 30 DAYS.
-THEN WHEN?

30:59.592 --> 31:01.225
WHEN, DADDY? EVER?

31:03.628 --> 31:05.429
HONEY...

31:05.431 --> 31:06.897
I JUST DON'T KNOW--

31:06.899 --> 31:08.098
BUT I KNOW!

31:08.100 --> 31:10.200
<i>I KNOW.</i>

31:10.202 --> 31:11.501
WHEN YOU LOVE SOMEBODY,

31:11.503 --> 31:12.970
YOU MARRY THEM.

31:12.972 --> 31:14.004
RIGHT, SHANE?

31:14.006 --> 31:16.106
UH...

31:16.108 --> 31:17.474
S-SOMEDAY...

31:17.476 --> 31:20.110
-MAYBE.
-I HATE "SOMEDAY"!

31:21.246 --> 31:23.614
COME ON.
LET'S GO GET MARRIED NOW.

31:23.616 --> 31:26.083
NOT LIKE THIS, ELLIE.

31:26.085 --> 31:27.484
BUT DON'T YOU WANT TO MARRY ME?

31:27.486 --> 31:29.219
I DO WANT TO MARRY YOU!

31:29.221 --> 31:31.255
BUT I DON'T WANT TO DO IT
LIKE THIS,

31:31.257 --> 31:33.423
WITHOUT EVERYBODY'S SUPPORT.

31:34.926 --> 31:37.227
EVERYBODY.

31:41.599 --> 31:43.934
[VOICE BREAKS]:
DOES THAT MEAN NO?

31:46.037 --> 31:48.038
[CRIES OUT]:
I QUIT!

31:48.040 --> 31:49.473
ELLIE!

31:50.675 --> 31:53.010
[♪]

31:54.545 --> 31:57.447
I KNEW IT WAS A MISTAKE
TO LET HER WORK HERE.

31:57.449 --> 31:59.983
MY CUSTOMERS
DON'T THINK SO.

31:59.985 --> 32:01.385
BOBBY?

32:01.387 --> 32:03.553
DID ELLIE ARRANGE THAT?

32:03.555 --> 32:06.290
[QUIET CHUCKLE]

32:06.292 --> 32:08.458
SHE DOES
ALL THE ONES WITH STARS.

32:08.460 --> 32:09.593
THAT'S HER SIGNATURE.

32:09.595 --> 32:11.328
[ASTONISHED CHUCKLE]

32:11.330 --> 32:12.362
THEY'RE...

32:12.364 --> 32:14.631
THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

32:14.633 --> 32:16.166
I'M-- I'M REALLY SUR--

32:16.168 --> 32:19.036
SURPRISED?

32:19.038 --> 32:21.638
I'M USED TO PEOPLE
WHO LOOK AT ME,

32:21.640 --> 32:23.140
AND THEY DON'T
UNDERSTAND.

32:23.142 --> 32:25.609
THEY DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHO I REALLY AM.

32:25.611 --> 32:29.479
THEY DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT I CAN REALLY DO.

32:29.481 --> 32:32.950
[VOICE SHAKES]:
BUT WHEN ELLIE...

32:32.952 --> 32:35.319
WHEN ELLIE LOOKS...

32:35.321 --> 32:36.486
WHEN ELLIE LOOKS AT YOU...

32:36.488 --> 32:37.654
SUDDENLY...

32:39.590 --> 32:42.125
YOU FEEL LIKE
SOMEBODY UNDERSTANDS.

32:43.361 --> 32:45.162
YES.

32:45.164 --> 32:46.530
REMEMBER THE YOKE

32:46.532 --> 32:48.265
YOU SHOWED US
IN THAT BARN?

32:48.267 --> 32:49.333
WHAT YOU SAID ABOUT

32:49.335 --> 32:52.102
PULLING TOGETHER,
SHARING THE LOAD?

32:52.104 --> 32:55.072
THERE'S A SONG
THAT I LOVE...

32:56.140 --> 32:57.708
ONE OF THE LINES WAS,

32:57.710 --> 33:01.712
"A MAN SHALL
LEAVE HIS MOTHER,

33:01.714 --> 33:03.180
"AND A WOMAN
LEAVE HER HOME.

33:03.182 --> 33:05.148
"THEY SHALL TRAVEL ON

33:05.150 --> 33:08.251
TO WHERE THE TWO SHALL BE AS ONE."

33:09.520 --> 33:11.254
I BELIEVE IT WORKS BEST

33:11.256 --> 33:14.591
WHEN THE TWO ARE EQUALLY YOKED, MR. KEMPERT.

33:14.593 --> 33:18.295
I BELIEVE  ELLIE AND BOBBY ARE...

33:18.297 --> 33:20.263
LET'S FACE IT.

33:20.265 --> 33:22.432
WE HAVE A LOT IN COMMON.

33:22.434 --> 33:23.633
[QUIET CHUCKLE]

33:26.771 --> 33:30.540
I REALLY MESSED THINGS UP.
DIDN'T I?

33:30.542 --> 33:33.176
[LAUGHS]
WELL, WELCOME TO MY WORLD.

33:34.212 --> 33:35.712
[CHUCKLES]

33:42.387 --> 33:45.222
[♪]

33:50.261 --> 33:52.062
-THERE YOU ARE.
-WHERE'S RITA?

33:52.064 --> 33:53.063
I WAS GONNA HELP HER
WITH HER MAKEUP.

33:53.065 --> 33:54.698
SHE'S IN
THE LADIES' CONVENIENCE.

33:54.700 --> 33:55.799
WELL, IT STARTS
ANY MINUTE.

33:55.801 --> 33:57.100
SHE'S CUTTING IT
VERY CLOSE.

33:59.337 --> 34:01.271
RITA! WHERE'S...

34:01.273 --> 34:02.739
YOUR DRESS?

34:02.741 --> 34:04.107
AND YOUR MAKEUP?

34:04.109 --> 34:05.609
YOUR...
YOUR EVERYTHING?

34:05.611 --> 34:07.544
I'M WEARING MY EVERYTHING.

34:07.546 --> 34:09.446
I...

34:09.448 --> 34:10.647
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

34:10.649 --> 34:12.783
I REALLY APPRECIATE YOUR HELP,
I DO,

34:12.785 --> 34:16.053
BUT THE PROBLEM IS,
IS THAT...

34:17.622 --> 34:19.790
WELL, IF THEY SEE THE NEW ME,

34:19.792 --> 34:22.559
THEY WON'T SEE THE REAL ME.

34:22.561 --> 34:24.494
WE SEE YOU, RITA.

34:24.496 --> 34:26.696
I CAN THINK OF
NO ONE TO BETTER

34:26.698 --> 34:28.565
TO REPRESENT ALL THAT
IS GOOD AND HONOURABLE

34:28.567 --> 34:30.534
IN THIS INSTITUTION.

34:31.702 --> 34:34.071
YOU WALK
INTO THAT ROOM TONIGHT

34:34.073 --> 34:37.174
KNOWING THAT
WE ARE ALL SO PROUD OF YOU.

34:39.677 --> 34:42.212
[QUIETLY]:
TO THINE OWN SELF BE TRUE.

34:44.315 --> 34:45.816
I'M SORRY, RITA.

34:45.818 --> 34:47.617
I WAS JUST TRYING
TO HELP YOU WIN.

34:47.619 --> 34:49.453
OH, I KNOW YOU WERE.

34:49.455 --> 34:52.489
THIS IS... THIS IS
THE ONLY WAY I KNOW HOW TO.

34:53.691 --> 34:57.094
BESIDES, WITH FRIENDS
LIKE YOU GUYS...

34:57.096 --> 34:59.162
I FEEL LIKE I'VE...

34:59.164 --> 35:01.398
-I'VE WON ALREADY.
-WELL, THEN GO GET 'EM!

35:01.400 --> 35:02.499
OH! [LAUGHS]

35:02.501 --> 35:03.600
OKAY!

35:03.602 --> 35:06.503
[♪]

35:12.777 --> 35:15.345
[♪]

35:19.417 --> 35:20.884
BREAK A LEG...

35:22.320 --> 35:25.655
AND I MEAN...
BREAK A LEG.

35:25.657 --> 35:26.690
"BUG."

35:26.692 --> 35:29.259
[♪]

35:33.131 --> 35:36.166
[♪]

35:40.872 --> 35:42.572
I FORGOT TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.

35:42.574 --> 35:44.374
WHAT?

35:44.376 --> 35:46.143
I-I'VE STARTED TAKING
A LIP-READING CLASS.

35:46.145 --> 35:47.544
HUH.

35:47.546 --> 35:51.248
YEAH. AND, UM, SOMETIMES,
IT COMES IN REAL HANDY.

35:51.250 --> 35:54.217
THAT'S VERY INTERESTING,
NORMAN, BUT I HAVE TO--

35:54.219 --> 35:55.017
YOU KNOW,

35:55.019 --> 35:57.787
MY FAVOURITE BUG
IS THE <i>DRYOCOCELUS AUSTRALIS</i> .

35:57.789 --> 35:59.222
PEOPLE IN THE SOUTH PACIFIC,

35:59.224 --> 36:00.457
THEY REFER TO IT
AS A "TREE LOBSTER".

36:00.459 --> 36:01.558
DO YOU KNOW WHY?

36:01.560 --> 36:03.293
WHY?

36:03.295 --> 36:05.896
BECAUSE IT HAS A HARD,
LOBSTER-LIKE EXOSKELETON,

36:05.898 --> 36:09.499
THAT MAKES IT
VIRTUALLY UNSQUASHABLE.

36:09.501 --> 36:11.668
HOW DO YOU NOT
LIKE A BUG LIKE THAT?

36:11.670 --> 36:14.371
[♪]

36:14.373 --> 36:15.739
[GIGGLES]

36:15.741 --> 36:17.474
[SIGHS]

36:17.476 --> 36:20.577
NORMAN, YOU ALWAYS
KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

36:20.579 --> 36:22.379
[JUDGE]:
AHEM. EXCUSE ME?

36:22.381 --> 36:24.581
IF WE COULD HAVE THE CONTESTANTS
PLEASE TAKE THEIR PLACES?

36:24.583 --> 36:26.349
THANK YOU.

36:26.351 --> 36:28.885
[♪]

36:30.354 --> 36:31.688
AND NOW WE'RE READY

36:31.690 --> 36:34.491
TO BEGIN OUR COMPULSORY
SORTING COMPETITION.

36:34.493 --> 36:35.926
WHERE'S MS. HAYWITH?

36:35.928 --> 36:37.494
I'M RIGHT HERE,
YOUR HONOUR.

36:37.496 --> 36:39.629
-OH!
-NO.

36:39.631 --> 36:41.398
NO SKATES.
THAT'S CHEATING.

36:41.400 --> 36:43.767
WELL, NOW,
THE RULES DO STATE

36:43.769 --> 36:45.302
THAT ENTRANTS ARE ENCOURAGED
TO BE CREATIVE

36:45.304 --> 36:47.204
AND TO USE THEIR INGENUITY,

36:47.206 --> 36:48.471
SO WE WILL ALLOW IT.

36:48.473 --> 36:49.506
[RITA]: OH!

36:49.508 --> 36:51.675
LADIES...
TO YOUR MARKS.

36:54.378 --> 36:55.779
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

36:55.781 --> 36:58.281
[♪]

37:00.885 --> 37:02.686
[♪]

37:27.545 --> 37:29.613
[♪]

37:34.552 --> 37:35.819
YEAH! [LAUGHING]

37:35.821 --> 37:37.954
[CROWD CHEERING]

37:41.292 --> 37:43.326
[JUDGE]: MS. HAYWITH,
THE SCORES INDICATE

37:43.328 --> 37:45.962
THAT AFTER YOUR TALENT
AND COMPULSORY EVENTS,

37:45.964 --> 37:47.797
YOU ARE CURRENTLY
IN SECOND PLACE.

37:47.799 --> 37:49.366
GOOD LUCK.

37:49.368 --> 37:52.869
OUR QUESTION FOR YOU
IS THIS...

37:52.871 --> 37:55.272
WE LIVE IN A CHANGING WORLD,

37:55.274 --> 37:56.806
AND THE FUTURE

37:56.808 --> 37:58.375
OF THE POSTAL SERVICE

37:58.377 --> 38:00.677
AND OF MAIL DELIVERY ITSELF
IS THREATENED.

38:00.679 --> 38:02.579
WHAT WORDS OF ENCOURAGEMENT
CAN YOU SHARE

38:02.581 --> 38:05.015
WITH YOUR FELLOW EMPLOYEES?

38:05.017 --> 38:07.584
WELL, I-I THINK--

38:07.586 --> 38:08.985
[GLYNIS COUGHS]

38:10.855 --> 38:13.356
[♪]

38:16.294 --> 38:17.060
[RITA STAMMERS, WORDS CATCH]

38:17.062 --> 38:18.795
[NORMAN]: AHEM.

38:18.797 --> 38:20.830
[♪]

38:24.769 --> 38:25.869
[QUIET CHUCKLE]

38:30.675 --> 38:32.409
SOME PEOPLE THINK

38:32.411 --> 38:35.979
THAT THE POST OFFICE IS A RELIC OF THE PAST,

38:35.981 --> 38:38.515
JUST WAITING TO BE SQUASHED LIKE A BUG

38:38.517 --> 38:39.916
BY ITS NEW COMPETITION.

38:39.918 --> 38:42.385
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

38:42.387 --> 38:43.753
BUGS CAN SURPRISE YOU.

38:45.089 --> 38:46.556
I THINK WE CAN

38:46.558 --> 38:48.658
LEARN A LOT FROM
THE SOUTH PACIFIC TREE LOBSTER.

38:50.061 --> 38:52.962
IT'S NOT BEAUTIFUL, LIKE A BUTTERFLY.

38:52.964 --> 38:56.700
IT CAN'T CREATE WHOLE SOCIETIES LIKE AN ANT,

38:56.702 --> 38:59.502
OR SPIN WEBS AND TRAP YOU...

38:59.504 --> 39:01.438
LIKE A SPIDER.

39:01.440 --> 39:04.541
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT CAN DO.

39:04.543 --> 39:06.743
BUT I KNOW WHAT IT CAN'T DO.

39:08.713 --> 39:11.915
ITS SHELL IS SO TOUGH,
THAT IT CAN'T BE SQUASHED.

39:14.018 --> 39:16.753
ONCE YOU KNOW HOW STRONG YOU ARE,

39:16.755 --> 39:18.121
THAT NO MATTER HOW TOUGH IT GETS,

39:18.123 --> 39:21.391
